Folks, <p>
I must chime in here on vets and Jane Fonda.  What people do not remember is that many, like Ms. Fonda, engaged in activities designed to shock people.  We in Vietnam Veterans Against the War (VVAW) did this as well, taking over the Statue of Liberty (twice) and throwing our medals back on the steps of the US Capitol building.  We were ready to try nearly anything to get the attention of the American people so they would force the government to bring our brothers and sisters home from that war.
